House Resolution 608
By: Representatives Lim of the 98th, Cannon of the 58th, and Carter of the 93rd
A RESOLUTION
1 Recognizing and commending the Metro Atlanta Coalition for Healthy Neighborhoods,
2 Wholesome Wave Georgia, and Retaaza; and for other purposes.
3 WHEREAS, the Metro Atlanta Coalition for Healthy Neighborhoods (MACHN) is a
4 dedicated partnership of organizations, including the Lucky Shoals Community Association,
5 working to address disparities in healthcare access, food security, and overall well-being
6 across metro Atlanta; and
7 WHEREAS, Wholesome Wave Georgia is dedicated to increasing access to fresh, locally
8 grown food for the 1.4 million food-insecure Georgians who rely on federal nutrition
9 assistance, thereby addressing the direct correlation between food insecurity, poverty, and
10 diet-related health issues such as obesity and chronic illness; and
11 WHEREAS, through innovative programs and partnerships with local farmers, Wholesome
12 Wave Georgia empowers families by making healthy food choices more affordable and
13 accessible; and
14 WHEREAS, Retaaza is a social enterprise that reduces food insecurity by connecting local
15 farmers directly with consumers, creating sustainable food pipelines that provide fresh,
