16 healthy produce to individuals and families in need while supporting economic stability in
17 rural communities and preventing food waste; and
18 WHEREAS, the American Heart Association (AHA), the nation's oldest and largest
19 voluntary organization dedicated to combating heart disease and stroke, has invested over
20 $5 billion in research, making it the largest not-for-profit funding source for cardiovascular
21 and cerebrovascular disease research aside from the federal government; and
22 WHEREAS, the Fulton-DeKalb Hospital Authority (FDHA) was established to ensure
23 equitable access to quality healthcare for all residents of Fulton and DeKalb counties
24 regardless of socioeconomic status by working collaboratively with and community partners
25 to close gaps in healthcare services and promote health equity; and
26 WHEREAS, it is abundantly fitting and proper that these exemplary organizations be
27 appropriately honored during this special time.
28 NOW, THEREFORE, BE IT RESOLVED BY THE HOUSE OF REPRESENTATIVES that
29 the members of this body recognize and commend the Metro Atlanta Coalition for Healthy
30 Neighborhoods, Wholesome Wave Georgia, and Retaaza for their contributions on behalf
31 of those in need as well as extend best wishes for continued success.
32 BE IT FURTHER RESOLVED that the Clerk of the House of Representatives is authorized
33 and directed to make appropriate copies of this resolution available for distribution to the
34 Metro Atlanta Coalition for Healthy Neighborhoods, Wholesome Wave Georgia, and
35 Retaaza.
